---
title: Chicken in Hollandaise Sauce with parsley butter potatoes and salad
description: The first documented recipe using hollandaise sauce is from as far back as the 1650s and hails from France. Hollandaise is most commonly used in breakfast dishes involving eggs, but in this dish, it's succulent chicken breast that's covered in the rich, golden glaze.
